<SUMMARY>
<!-- PJG ITAG l=10 g=1 f=2 -->
SUMMARY: 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=10 g=1 f=1 -->
The Food and Drug Administration (FDA) is announcing that it is withdrawing an advance notice of proposed rulemaking
(ANPRM) on the regulation of dietary supplements that it published in the 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=10 g=1 f=4 -->
Federal Register
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=10 g=1 f=1 -->
 of June 18, 1993 (58 FR 33690) (hereinafter referred to as the June 18, 1993, ANPRM). This action is necessary because
of recently enacted legislation and terminates the rulemaking initiated by the ANPRM.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 02 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

