<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=81 g=1 f=3 -->
2. Affected Sources 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
For purposes of this rulemaking, the affected source 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
would be considered the aggregate of all operations at a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
shipbuilding facility. A new operation at a shipbuilding 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
facility would not be considered a new source. Instead, it 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
may qualify as a modification of the existing source. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 The proposed standards would limit VOHAP emissions from 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
indoor and outdoor coating operations. The VOHAP emissions 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
result largely from solvent evaporation from the coatings. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
These emissions occur during application and drying/curing. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Due to the size of ships and their components, most coatings 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
are applied outdoors. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 The proposed standards would also reduce VOHAP 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
emissions from handling, transfer, use, and storage of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
VOHAP-containing materials through work practice measures. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
These emissions also occur as a result of solvent 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
evaporation. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=3 -->
B. Standards 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
The proposed standards would be the same for new and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
existing facilities. (See section VII.B. for discussion on 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the basis for the standards.) The proposed standards would 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
impose limits on the VOHAP content of 23 types of coatings 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
used at shipbuilding facilities. (See section VII.C. for a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
list of the proposed limits.) The limits would be stated in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
terms of mass of VOHAP per volume of coating less water and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
less negligibly photochemically reactive (exempt) compounds. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Compliance with the VOHAP limits must be demonstrated on a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
monthly basis. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 The proposed standards would allow for an alternative 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
means of compliance other than using compliant coatings, if 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
approved by the Administrator. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 The proposed standards would also require that all 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
handling and transfer of VOHAP containing materials to and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
from containers, tanks, vats, vessels, and piping systems be 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
conducted in a manner that minimizes spills and other 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
factors leading to emissions. In addition, containers of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
thinning solvent or waste that hold any VOHAP must be 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
normally closed (to minimize evaporation) unless materials 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
are being added to or removed from them. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=3 -->
C. Compliance Dates 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
The proposed rule would require compliance for existing 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
affected sources within 1 year after the effective date of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the rule. An existing unaffected area source that increases 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
its HAP emissions (or potential to emit) such that it 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
becomes a major source would be required to comply within 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
1 year after becoming a major source. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 Any new or reconstructed sources would be required to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
adhere to the compliance schedule in the General Provisions 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&sect;63.6(b) of subpart A without any modification. For new 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
or reconstructed affected sources whose startup date is 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
before the effective date of the rule, the compliance date 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
is the effective date of the rule. For new or reconstructed 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
affected sources whose startup date is after the effective 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
date of the rule, the compliance date is the startup date. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
A new unaffected area source that increases its emissions 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(or potential to emit) such that it becomes a major source 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
would be required to comply immediately upon becoming a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
major source. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=3 -->
D. Compliance Procedures 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
The proposed rule would allow affected sources to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
choose among five options for demonstrating compliance with 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the VOHAP standards. Their choice will be influenced by the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
perceived need to add ``thinning'' solvent (thinner) to alter 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the viscosity of the coating in order to spray effectively. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(For the purposes of this proposed regulation, thinner is 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
defined as any liquid material added to a coating.) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Regardless of the option(s) chosen, affected sources would 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
first be required to determine the coating category 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e.g., general use, air flask, antenna, etc.), the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
applicable VOHAP limit, and the VOC content for each batch 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
of coating received from the manufacturer.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
