<DOCNO> FR941206-1-00096 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR941206-1-00008 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
A source may demonstrate compliance either by showing 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
that the VOC content is less than the VOHAP limit 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(options 1&hyph;4) or by the use of option 5 (discussed below) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
which would measure the actual VOHAP content. If the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
shipyard is subject to regulatory limits on the VOC content 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
of its coatings, the primary compliance method for this rule 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
would be to certify the VOC content of each container of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
coating, as applied. (That information would then be used 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
to determine compliance with the applicable VOHAP limit 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
using any of the options 1&hyph;4.) Certification of VOC content 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
is done by: (1) using Method 24 of 40 CFR part 60, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
appendix A; (2) using forms similar to those included in the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
certification procedure published in EPA&hyph;450/3&hyph;84&hyph;019 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(revised 6/86), ``Procedures for Certifying Quantity of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Volatile Organic Compounds Emitted by Paint, Ink, and Other 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Coatings''; or (3) an alternative method approved by the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Administrator. Option 5 may be used for demonstrating 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
compliance when a shipyard is not subject to VOC limits. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 Affected sources would be allowed to use the following 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
methods to demonstrate compliance to avoid testing every 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
container of coating; however, any analysis of an individual 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
container of coating using the Agency's Method 24 would take 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
precedence to determine or to verify a violation. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Paragraphs (i) through (iii) are summaries of options 1, 2, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
and 3. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 (i) Shipyards can demonstrate compliance of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
as-supplied VOC content as certified by the manufacturer. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
If the as-supplied coating is used without adding thinning 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
solvent, shipyards can certify that the as-applied VOC 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
content of the batch of coating is identical to the as-supplied VOC content, if it were certified by the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
manufacturer. If the certified VOC content is less than the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
VOHAP limit, compliance is demonstrated. (``As applied'' 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
means after any thinning by the user or just prior to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
application to the substrate. ``As supplied'' means as 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
supplied by the coating manufacturer.) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 (ii) Shipyards can demonstrate compliance if the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
actual volume of thinner used is less than the maximum 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
allowable volume of thinner on a coating-by-coating basis. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 (iii) Shipyards can demonstrate compliance by 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
comparing the actual volume of thinner used to the maximum 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
allowable volume on a ``group'' basis. A group of coatings 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
would be defined as those which use the same thinner. (See 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
section VII.E. for more explanation.) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 Compliance with options 1 through 4 is based on the VOC 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
content of each container of coating, as applied. If the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
as-applied VOC content is less than or equal to the VOHAP 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
limit, then compliance would be demonstrated (See 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
part III.E. for how ``exempt'' compounds which are HAP are 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
considered in compliance determinations and other details). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 Shipyards can also demonstrate compliance by measuring 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the actual VOHAP content of a coating. If the as-applied 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
VOHAP content is less than or equal to the alternate VOHAP 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
limit, then compliance would be demonstrated. (See II.E., 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Option 5, for how alternate VOHAP limits are determined). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(Concurrently with this rule, the Agency is preparing 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
requirements for sample preparation and the performance 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
specifications required of an acceptable analytical 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
procedure.) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
