<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
The test methods and procedures described in the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
previous section will be used to determine compliance. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Failure to meet the emission limits as measured by these 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
procedures would be an enforceable violation of the emission 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
limits of the standard. When add-on controls are used, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
monitoring shall be capable of detecting deviations from 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
each applicable emission limitation or other standard with 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
sufficient reliability and timeliness to determine 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
continuous compliance over the applicable reporting period. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 Although the term ``continuous'' generally means at all 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
times, the Agency has determined that less frequent 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
measurements or determinations of compliance can ensure 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
continuous compliance. The potential variability of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
emissions or parameters is a primary factor in establishing 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the frequency of measurements. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=3 -->
G. Notification Requirements 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
The proposed rule would require affected sources to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
follow the notification requirements in &sect;&sect;63.9(a)-(d) and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(h)-(j) of subpart A of the general provisions. In addition 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
to the initial notification requirements in &sect;&sect;63.9(b)(2) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
and (3) of subpart A, sources would be required to include 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
in the initial notification: (1) the compliance 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
procedure(s) that they intend to use; (2) procedures for 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
ensuring compliance with the handling, transfer, and storage 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
standard; and (3) procedures for maintaining records. These 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
are subject to the approval of the Administrator. In 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
addition, they would be required to submit a notification of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
compliance status on a quarterly basis, with any exceedances 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
reported on a quarterly basis. Following the first year, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the owner or operator of a source that has had no 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
exceedances for a full year (can be any year after the first 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
year), may request Administrator approval to reduce the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
frequency of notification to semiannual. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=3 -->
H. Recordkeeping and Reporting Requirements 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
The proposed rule would require affected sources to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
follow the general recordkeeping and reporting requirements 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
in &sect;&sect;63.10(a)-(b) and (f) of subpart A of the general 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
provisions. Sections 63.10(c)-(e) of subpart A do not apply 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
unless a source uses a control device to comply with the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
standards except for the excess emission report required by 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&sect;63.10(e)(3) which applies regardless of how emissions are 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
controlled. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 In addition, each owner or operator of an affected 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
source would be required to certify annually that all 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
personnel involved with coatings, thinning of coatings, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
keeping coating records, or handling/transferring VOHAP-containing materials have received the training required
by 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the regulation. A record of the certification is required, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
but no report is required. The purpose of the certification 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
is to ensure that the training does occur at least once per 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
year, and that documentation does exit for an enforcement 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
official to review. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 Affected sources would be required to keep all records 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
needed to demonstrate compliance with the standards, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
including calculations and records of any Method 24 or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
alternate VOHAP tests. All records would be compiled each 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
calendar month and compliance status determined every month. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
In addition, a source is required to report on a quarterly 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
basis any exceedances to the EPA and to provide in the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
excess emissions report the data needed to confirm and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
quantify the reported exceedance. All records must be 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
maintained for a minimum of 5 years. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 The quarterly report should include: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 1. A summary of the number and duration of deviations 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
during the reporting period classified by reason, including 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
known causes for which a Federally-approved or promulgated 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
exemption from an emission limitation or standard may apply; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 2. Identification of the data availability achieved 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
during the reporting period, including a summary of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
number and total duration of incidents during which the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
monitoring protocol failed to operate in accordance with 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
design or produced data that did not meet minimum data 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
accuracy and precision requirements (classified by reason); 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 3. Identification of the compliance status as of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
last day of the reporting period and whether compliance was 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
continuous or intermittent during the reporting period; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 4. If, pursuant to (2) of this section, the owner or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
operator identifies any deviation as resulting from a known 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
cause for which no Federally-approved or promulgated 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
exemption from an emission limitation or standard applies, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the monitoring report shall also include all records that 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the source is required to maintain that pertain to the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
periods during which such deviation occurred and: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 a. The magnitude of each deviation; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 b. The reason for each deviation; 
