<!-- PJG ITAG l=85 g=1 f=1 -->
V. National Emission Standards for Hazardous Air 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Pollutants (NESHAP) Decision Process 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
A. Source of Authority for NESHAP Development 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Section 112 of the Act gives the EPA the authority to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
establish national standards to reduce HAP emissions from 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
sources that emit one or more HAP. Section 112(b) contains 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
a list of the specific HAP to be regulated by NESHAP. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Section 112(c) directs the EPA to use this pollutant list to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
develop and publish a list of source categories for which 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
NESHAP will be developed. The Act defines major sources as 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
those that emit or have the potential to emit considering 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
controls, in the aggregate, 9.1 Mg/yr (10 tons/yr) or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
greater of individual HAP or 22.7 Mg/yr (25 tons/yr) or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
greater of any combination of HAP. The initial list of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
source categories was published on July 16, 1992 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(57 FR 31576). Shipyards (major sources only) appear on 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
this list. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Area sources are those sources that are not major 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
sources. Area source categories selected by the EPA for 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
NESHAP development will be based on the Administrator's 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
judgment that the sources in a category, individually or in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the aggregate, pose a ``threat of adverse effects to health 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
and the environment.'' The EPA will continue to evaluate 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
whether area source shipyards should be added to the list of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
area source categories. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
B. Criteria for Development of NESHAP 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The NESHAP are to be developed to control HAP emissions 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
from both new and existing sources according section 112(d) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
of the Act. The standards are to reflect the maximum degree 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
of reduction that is achievable for new or existing sources. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The NESHAP must reflect consideration of the cost of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
achieving the emission reduction, nonair quality health and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
environmental impacts, and energy requirements for control 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
levels more stringent than the MACT floor (described below). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The Act specifies that emission reduction may be 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
accomplished through application of measures, processes, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
methods, systems or techniques, including, but not limited 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
to, measures which:
