<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Any new or reconstructed sources would be required to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
adhere to the compliance schedule in &sect;63.6(b) of subpart A 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
of the general provisions. For new or reconstructed sources 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
whose startup date is before the effective date of the rule, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the compliance date would be the effective date of the rule. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
For new or reconstructed sources whose startup date is after 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the effective date of the rule, the compliance date would be 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the startup date. A new unaffected area source that 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
increases its emissions (or potential to emit) such that it 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
becomes a major source would be required to comply 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
immediately upon becoming a major source. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Many shipyards in California have been complying with 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
VOC limits equal to those in the proposed BACM since 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
September 1991. Hence, coatings that meet the limits should 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
be readily available. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
E. Selection of Compliance Procedures 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The proposed rule would allow affected sources to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
choose from five options for demonstrating compliance with 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the VOHAP standards. Regardless of the option(s) chosen, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
for each coating, affected sources would be required to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
first determine: (1) its coating category in Table 1 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e.g., general use, air flask, antenna, etc.), (2) the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
applicable VOHAP limit, and (3) the VOC (or VOHAP) content 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
for each manufactured batch of coating. The VOC (or VOHAP) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
content of the batch would be determined through 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
certification as explained in part III.D. (It is in the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
best interest of affected sources to use manufacturers that 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
certify their coatings.) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
For options 1 through 4 involving VOC content 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
determinations, the compliance method is the Agency's 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Method 24. Affected sources would be allowed any of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
methods described below to avoid testing every container. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The ultimate referee method, however, is Method 24. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Option 5 involves VOHAP content determinations; the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
compliance method has to be approved by the Administrator 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
and comply with EPA requirements for sample preparation. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The proposed rule does not specify compliance 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
procedures for the handling, transfer, and storage standard. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Each affected source would be required to develop and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
include specific compliance procedures for their facility in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the initial notification to the Administrator. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
An affected source would be allowed to select any of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the following methods for compliance and may choose to use 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
only one of the options for all coatings at the facility or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
use a combination of options. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=81 g=1 f=1 -->
Option 1. Certification of Each Container or Coating, As-Applied 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Procedures for certifying the quantity of VOC emitted 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
by paints, ink, and other coatings are combined in the EPA 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
publication 450/3&hyph;84&hyph;019 (revised 6/86). Compliance with 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the VOHAP content limits would be achieved by sampling, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
testing, and certifying the VOC content of each container of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
coating, as applied. If the as-applied VOC content is less 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
than or equal to the VOHAP limit in Table 1, the coating 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
complies. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=81 g=1 f=1 -->
Option 2. Coatings To Which Thinning Solvent Will Not Be Added 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
If thinning solvents will not be added to the coating 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
under any circumstances, the affected source may demonstrate 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
compliance with the VOHAP content limit by certifying the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
as-applied VOC content by manufacturer's batch. The as- 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
applied certification may be based on a coating that has 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
been certified by the manufacturer as to the as-supplied 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
content and simply requires documentation that no thinning 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
solvent was added to the coating. No additional testing 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
would be necessary. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
All painters would have to be notified that no thinning 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
solvent may be added to the coating before application. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
This notification may be accomplished through a label 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
affixed to each container in the batch or through another 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
means of notification specified in the source's initial 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
notification that is required in &sect;63.9(b) of subpart A of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the general provisions. Other means of notifying painters 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
may include use of a bar coding system or posting of a list 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
of coatings that should not have thinning solvents added. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
This option is the least burdensome to affected 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
sources, but it may only be used for coatings that will not 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
be thinned. However, any Method 24 tests on individual 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
containers of coating, as applied, that show noncompliance 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
with the standards would take precedence and indicate a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
violation.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
