<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Inasmuch as shipyards may use the same solvent to reduce more than one category of coating, this option was created
to minimize recordkeeping in such cases. The group compliance option is similar to the coating-by-coating compliance
option, except the source does not need to maintain thinner usage by individual paint category; it would be allowed
to calculate the total allowable volume of thinner used for a group of coatings. A group would be constituted based
on use of common thinner. A group could consist of two or more different batches of the same coating or different coatings.
For example, a group may consist of a certain batch of antenna coating combined with all batches of general use coatings.
However, a group may not contain any coating to which thinning solvent will not be added. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Affected sources would calculate the maximum allowable 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
dilution ratio for each coating using equation 1 or 2. All 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
painters would have to be notified of the maximum allowable 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
dilution ratio for each coating. Beginning with the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
recorded amount of coating used during the previous month, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the facility would calculate the net allowable volume of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
thinner that could have been used by each coating in the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
group. If the actual usage was less than or equal to the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
net allowable volume for the group, the source is in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
compliance. However, any Method 24 test on individual 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
containers of coating, as applied, that shows noncompliance 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
with the standards would take precedence and indicate a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
violation. Equations 1 through 3 were derived from the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
EPA's ``Procedures for Certifying Quantity of Volatile 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Organic Compounds Emitted by Paint, Ink, and Other Coatings'' 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(Revised June 1986), EPA_450/3&hyph;84&hyph;019. 
