<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
F. Selection of Test Methods and Procedures 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Since the EPA does not yet have a published reference 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
method for analyzing for the amount of VOHAP in a coating, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the measure of total VOC is to be used as a surrogate. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Method 24 is the Agency's reference method for determining 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the total volatile organic content (the total amount of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
VOHAP and other volatile organics). The proposed rule would 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
use the VOC content of as-applied coatings to determine 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
compliance with the VOHAP content limits (see 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
section VII.B.1). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Most, if not all, major shipbuilding facilities are 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
believed to be located in ozone nonattainment areas. These 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
facilities are likely to be required to meet State VOC 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
regulations requiring BACM. As explained earlier in this 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
notice, the EPA's draft recommended BACM for the draft CTG 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
contains VOC limits equivalent to the VOHAP limits being 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
proposed. Thus, using Method 24 to measure compliance with 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
both the VOC and HAP rules (i.e., one test to satisfy two 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
concerns) should be the least burdensome route of any source 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
having to meet VOC rules in addition to HAP rules. However, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
in case there are any sources which are not required to meet 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
VOC rules and have a desire to determine compliance through 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
measuring VOHAP instead of VOC, an approach as outlined in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
option 5 is being proposed. (Comments are requested.) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The proposed rule would require that affected sources 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
use forms and procedures comparable to those in the EPA's 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
``Procedures for Certifying Quantity of Volatile Organic 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Compounds Emitted by Paint, Ink and Other Coatings,'' 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(Revised June 1986) EPA&hyph;450/3&hyph;84&hyph;019 for all certifications 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
needed for compliance demonstrations. Consistent use of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
these forms and procedures will provide uniform and complete 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
records that will allow determination of ``continuous'' 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
compliance with the standards. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Procedures other than test methods would be required to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
demonstrate compliance with the handling, transfer, and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
storage standard. Each source is required to submit an 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
implementation plan that will include specific procedures to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
ensure compliance. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
G. Selection of Notification, Recordkeeping, and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Reporting Requirements 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=81 g=1 f=1 -->
1. Notification Requirements 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The proposed rule would require affected sources to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
submit an initial notification and subsequent quarterly 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
notifications of compliance status. Exceedances 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(violations) should be reported on a quarterly basis. The 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
notification requirements in &sect;&sect;63.9 (a)&hyph;(d) and (h)&hyph;(j) of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
subpart A would apply to all affected sources in addition to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the source category-specific requirements in the proposed 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
rule. Sections 63.9 (e)&hyph;(g) of subpart A would not apply 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
unless an affected source installs an add-on control device. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Section 63.9(b) of subpart A contains the initial 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
notification requirements. The initial notification would 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
alert the Administrator of: (1) The applicability for 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
existing facilities or of construction for new facilities, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) how the source plans to comply with the proposed 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
standards, and (3) if any delays in compliance are expected. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
This notification would be due no later than 120 calendar 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
days after the effective date of the rule for existing 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
sources; for new or reconstructed sources, the due date 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
would be within 120 days after initial startup if approval 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
of construction or reconstruction is not required under 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&sect;63.5(d) of subpart A. In addition to the items listed in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&sect;63.9(b) of subpart A, sources would be required to include 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
in the initial notification: (1) The compliance 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
procedure(s) that they intend to use for the coating 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
operation standards; (2) procedures for ensuring compliance 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
with the handling, transfer, and storage standard; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) procedures for maintaining records. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Section 63.9(h) of subpart A contains the requirements 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
for notification of compliance status. These would notify 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the Administrator of whether compliance has been achieved 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
over the past 3 months. These notifications would be due 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
before the 60th day following completion of each 3-month 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
period. If there are no violations within the first year, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
compliant sources may request permission from the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Administrator to go to 6-month notifications. Because 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
records would be compiled on a monthly basis, 60 days should 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
provide sufficient time to prepare these notifications. In 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
addition to the items listed in &sect;63.9(h) of subpart A, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
affected sources would be required to include in these 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
notifications all other records that the source is required 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
to maintain and compile on a monthly basis according to the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
proposed rule.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
