<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=81 g=1 f=1 -->
2. Recordkeeping and Reporting Requirements 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The proposed rule would require affected sources to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
maintain adequate records to verify the compliance status of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the source on a monthly basis. The recordkeeping and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
reporting requirements of the general provisions in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&sect;&sect;63.10 (a)&hyph;(b) and (f) of subpart A would apply to all 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
affected sources. The source category-specific requirements 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
in the proposed rule also apply. Sections 63.10 (c)&hyph;(e) of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
subpart A would not apply unless an affected source installs 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
an add-on control. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Affected sources would be required to keep records for 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
5 years of all VOC content certifications, VOHAP content 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
certifications, maximum allowable dilution ratios, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
quantities of coatings and thinner consumed, and compliance 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
calculations needed to determine compliance with the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
standards. These records would vary slightly depending on 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the method(s) of determining compliance under &sect;63.784 that 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the source chooses to use. Records of any Method 24 tests 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(or VOHAP tests) conducted on individual coatings, as 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
applied, would also be maintained. These records are 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
required in case the results of any such test conflicts with 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the results of any compliance determination conducted in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
accordance with the other allowable methods. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The Administrator believes that the records required 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
under the proposed rule are necessary for a regulatory 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
agency to determine the compliance status of an affected 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
source efficiently and effectively. All records would be 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
compiled each calendar month and maintained for a minimum of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
