<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Under Executive Order 12866 (58 FR 51735 (October 4, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
1993)), the Agency must determine whether the regulatory 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
action is ``significant'' and therefore subject to OMB review 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
and the requirements of the Executive Order. The Order 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
defines ``significant regulatory action'' as one that is 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
likely to result in a rule that may: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 1. Have an annual effect on the economy of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
$100 million or more or adversely affect in a material way 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the economy, a sector of the economy, productivity, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
competition, jobs, the environment, public health or safety, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
or State, local, or tribal governments or communities; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 2. Create a serious inconsistency or otherwise 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
interfere with an action taken or planned by another agency; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 3. Materially alter the budgetary impact of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
