and appropriate requirement (i.e., an ARAR) for Superfund response actions. However, as a codified policy reflecting
substantial scientific and technical evaluation, it has been considered as important guidance in developing cleanup
levels at Superfund sites. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
In August 1990, EPA issued several CERCLA guidance documents regarding remediation of PCBs at Superfund sites. Among
other provisions, these guidance documents establish guidelines for the CERCLA Program to follow in setting preliminary
remediation goals for PCBs for soil, ground water, and sediment contaminated with PCBs at Superfund sites. (See ``A
Guide on Remedial Actions at Superfund Sites with PCB Contamination'', OSWER Directive No. 9355.4&hyph;01 FS (August
1990) [``PCB Guide''].) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
