cleanups, because the rule would provide three options. Generally, EPA would be likely to select the risk-based option
at 761.61(c), which would give the Agency very broad discretion in selecting a remedy. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
One commenter suggested that EPA should conduct a comparative risk analysis of all possible disposal techniques
and include other factors such as transportation and disposal of treatment residues before issuing a PCB disposal
approval under TSCA. EPA does not believe that TSCA authority should be used to accomplish exactly what CERCLA, an
