and various other materials. Demolition wastes may contain any number of materials, including some of the same materials
found in shredder waste. The results of shredding or demolition processes may be that the sources of PCB contamination
in these large volume wastes may not easily be identified. In addition, some decommissioning projects and demolition
projects may produce large quantities of insulation containing PCBs. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
