way into the scrap metal stream, and may result in subsequent contamination of shredder waste. EPA acknowledges the
need for responsibly operated metal recycling facilities. As such, EPA is reiterating that all wastes containing
50 ppm PCBs or greater, including shredder wastes, as well as demolition wastes and large volumes of other PCB non-remediation
wastes impregnated with PCBs (e.g., insulation), are regulated for disposal. However, EPA is proposing at 761.62
