 Section 6(e) of the Toxic Substances Control Act (TSCA) bans the manufacture, processing, distribution in commerce,
and the use of PCBs unless the PCBs are totally enclosed. Section 6(e) gives EPA authority, however, to authorize these
PCB activities if the Administrator finds that they will not present an unreasonable risk of injury to health or the
environment. TSCA provides that EPA may set terms and conditions, including recordkeeping and reporting requirements,
for granting an exemption. 
